Course: Applied Machine Learning

======================================================================
1. PROJECT OBJECTIVE
======================================================================

The objective of this project is to apply Unsupervised Learning techniques 
to segment customers based on their purchasing behavior and demographics. 
This analysis will help the business:

1. Identify distinct customer groups for targeted marketing
2. Understand spending patterns across different segments
3. Develop personalized strategies for each customer group
4. Improve customer retention and increase sales

Business Impact:
Customer segmentation allows businesses to:
- Send personalized offers to each segment
- Optimize marketing spend by targeting the right customers
- Improve customer satisfaction through relevant communications
- Increase customer lifetime value through better engagement

Target Stakeholders:
- Marketing Team: For campaign design and targeting
- Sales Team: For personalized customer interactions
- Product Team: For product development and pricing
- Senior Management: For strategic decision-making

======================================================================
2. PROJECT PLANNING AND METHODOLOGY
======================================================================

Analytical Workflow:
This project follows a structured unsupervised learning workflow:

Phase 1: Data Understanding
- Explore dataset structure, quality, and patterns
- Identify relevant features for clustering
- Assess data completeness and consistency

Phase 2: Data Preprocessing
- Handle missing values (if any)
- Scale features for fair comparison
- Prepare data for clustering algorithms

Phase 3: Model Development
- Test multiple clustering algorithms
- Vary hyperparameters for each method
- Train at least 3 variations of each method

Phase 4: Model Evaluation
- Compare using silhouette score
- Evaluate using Calinski-Harabasz index
- Assess using Davies-Bouldin score

Phase 5: Interpretation
- Profile each identified cluster
- Derive business insights
- Provide actionable recommendations

Why Unsupervised Learning?
Unsupervised learning is chosen because:
- We don't have pre-labeled customer segments to predict
- We want to discover natural groupings in the data
- Clustering reveals hidden patterns in customer behavior
- Results can directly inform marketing strategy

