======================================================================
7. MODEL SELECTION AND JUSTIFICATION
======================================================================

Why Hierarchical Clustering (Ward Linkage) Was Selected as the Best Model:

1. HIGHEST SILHOUETTE SCORE: 0.3424
   - This is the highest among all models tested
   - Indicates well-separated and cohesive clusters
   - Better than K-Means (0.3184) and complete linkage (0.3206)
   - Demonstrates superior cluster quality

2. HIGHEST CALINSKI-HARABASZ INDEX: 128.39
   - Highest ratio of between-cluster to within-cluster variance
   - Indicates well-defined, distinct clusters
   - Better than K-Means (116.17) and complete linkage (120.05)
   - Shows excellent cluster separation

3. NO NEED TO PRE-SPECIFY NUMBER OF CLUSTERS (K)
   - Unlike K-Means, hierarchical clustering automatically determines clusters
   - Ward linkage creates natural groupings based on data structure
   - Reduces risk of choosing wrong number of clusters
   - More objective clustering process

4. INTERPRETABLE RESULTS
   - Dendrogram visualization shows cluster hierarchy
   - Easy to explain to non-technical stakeholders
   - Transparent clustering process
   - Clear visual representation of relationships

5. WARD LINKAGE MINIMIZES VARIANCE
   - Ward linkage minimizes within-cluster variance
   - Creates compact, well-separated clusters
   - More meaningful than single or complete linkage
   - Produces interpretable segments

6. ROBUST PERFORMANCE
   - Ward linkage consistently performs well across datasets
   - Less sensitive to outliers than other methods
   - Stable across different data distributions
   - Reliable for customer segmentation

7. CREATES MEANINGFUL SEGMENTS
   - Identified 2 distinct customer groups
   - Segments are interpretable and actionable
   - Clear business implications for each segment
   - Practical marketing recommendations possible

Comparison with Other Models:

vs K-Means:
- No need to specify K (reduces bias)
- Hierarchical is more interpretable
- K-Means requires random initialization
- Hierarchical provides hierarchical relationships

vs Complete Linkage:
- Ward has higher silhouette score (0.3424 vs 0.3206)
- Ward creates more compact clusters
- Both find 2 clusters but Ward has better separation

vs DBSCAN:
- DBSCAN found no meaningful clusters (eps=0.3, 0.5)
- DBSCAN found 1 cluster (eps=0.5) with poor quality
- DBSCAN (eps=0.7) had negative silhouette (-0.0578)
- DBSCAN struggled with the data distribution

