======================================================================
9. LIMITATIONS
======================================================================

Detailed Limitations Analysis:

Limitation 1: Small Dataset Size
- Only 200 customers included in the analysis
- May not represent all customer types and segments
- Results may not generalize to larger population
- Less statistical power for finding subtle patterns
- Limited confidence in segment stability
- Impact: High - Affects generalizability

Limitation 2: Synthetic Data
- Data is generated, not real customer behavior
- May not reflect actual customer patterns and preferences
- Business recommendations may not be accurate
- Limited real-world applicability
- Patterns may be artificial or simplified
- Impact: High - Affects practical relevance

Limitation 3: Limited Features
- Only 3 features used for clustering
- Missing important variables:
  - Purchase frequency and recency
  - Product categories and preferences
  - Shopping channel (online vs. in-store)
  - Customer service interactions
  - Demographic details (location, occupation)
  - Seasonal purchase patterns
- Impact: Medium - May miss important segment differentiators

Limitation 4: No Temporal Data
- Can't track behavior over time
- No seasonality or trend analysis
- Static snapshot of customers
- Can't identify changing behaviors
- Can't predict future value
- Impact: Medium - Limits predictive capability

Limitation 5: No Validation
- Segments not validated with business metrics
- No A/B testing performed
- Marketing recommendations are theoretical
- Business impact not measured
- Effectiveness not confirmed
- Impact: Medium - Limits confidence in recommendations

Limitation 6: Single Method Approach
- Only clustering methods tested
- No ensemble or hybrid approaches
- Could benefit from multiple techniques
- Limited perspective on segmentation
- Impact: Low - Could improve with more methods

Limitation 7: Algorithm Limitations
- K-Means: Requires K, sensitive to initialization
- Hierarchical: Expensive for large datasets
- DBSCAN: Parameter sensitivity
- Impact: Low - Managed through multiple variations

Limitation 8: Class Imbalance
- Segments are relatively balanced (47%/53%)
- No severe imbalance issues
- However, small dataset limits confidence
- Impact: Low - No severe imbalance issues

